{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"8c86ede03c8e80b0dad5131138f96e957a4ee66b"},"timestamp":1380772029,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyMDQzNTk2Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/993","origin":"github"},"title":".namespace rooting incorrectly documented","message":"docs/book/pir/ch04_variables.pod and docs/pdds/pdd19_pir.pod both document that the namespace declared with .namespace is relative to the root namespace, and that \".namespace []\" refers to the root namespace. This is not correct. In fact .namespace is relative to the HLL namespace.\n\nDemonstration:\n\n```\n$ cat t22.pir\n.HLL \"foo\"\n.namespace [\"bar\"]\n.sub main :main\n        $P0 = get_namespace\n        $P1 = get_root_namespace [\"bar\"]\n        eq_addr $P0, $P1, root_eq\n        say \"root ne\"\n        goto root_done\n        root_eq:\n        say \"root eq\"\n        root_done:\n        $P2 = get_hll_namespace [\"bar\"]\n        eq_addr $P0, $P2, hll_eq\n        say \"hll ne\"\n        goto hll_done\n        hll_eq:\n        say \"hll eq\"\n        hll_done:\n.end\n$ ./parrot t22.pir\nroot ne\nhll eq\n```\n\n-zefram","files":null}]}